South Africa's State-Mining Company Set to Start Output, Business Day Says

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-02-17T05:01:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/south-africa-s-state-mining-company-set-to-start-output-business-day-says.html
African Exploration Mining and
Finance Corp., the state-owned South African mining company,
will open its first mine within a month, Business Day said,
citing Department of Mineral Resources Director General Sandile
Nogxina.  Funding will be received from the Industrial Development
Corp., the Johannesburg-based newspaper said. Nogxina declined
to say what minerals would be mined, Business Day said.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
